# Responsibilities

## boot.ts

* Initialize app
* Initialize monetization system
* Mount WebView
* Mount Offline component

No business logic here.

---

## core/monetization.ts

Single orchestrator.

Responsibilities:

* init()
* purchaseRemoveAds()
* restorePurchases()
* refreshEntitlements()
* determine isPro
* enable/disable ads based on isPro

State exposed:

{
isPro: boolean
adsEnabled: boolean
}

RevenueCat → entitlement
Entitlement → ad state

No UI logic inside.

---

## providers/revenuecat.ts

Thin wrapper around RevenueCat SDK:

* init()
* purchase(productId)
* restore()
* getEntitlements()

No app logic. No ad logic.

---

## providers/admob.ts

Thin wrapper around AdMob plugin:

* init()
* showBanner()
* hideBanner()
* setEnabled(boolean)

No entitlement logic.

---

## network/offline.tsx

* Subscribe to Capacitor Network plugin
* Track isOnline
* Render blocking modal if offline
* No business logic

---

# Flow

1. App boots
2. RevenueCat initialized
3. Entitlements fetched
4. If pro:

   * Disable ads
   * Hide banner
5. If not pro:

   * Enable ads
   * Show banner

On purchase:

* Call RevenueCat purchase
* Refresh entitlements
* Re-evaluate ad state

On restore:

* Restore
* Refresh entitlements
* Re-evaluate ad state

---

# Engineering Constraints

* No cross-module circular dependencies
* No global mutable state outside monetization module
* All async flows awaited properly
* No silent failures
* Clear error logging
* Deterministic ad suppression

---

# Quality Bar

The project should demonstrate:

* Clean separation of concerns
* Controlled side effects
* Clear orchestration layer
* Real-world edge case handling (offline, restore)

Not:

* Feature breadth
* Over-configuration
* Fancy abstraction

